  "prompt": "Can I deactivate my Roku device?",
  "response": "Yes, you can deactivate your Roku device. Here's a step-by-step guide on how to do it:\n\n1. **Go to the Roku website**: Open your web browser and navigate to the Roku website (www.roku.com).\n\n2. **Sign in to your Roku account**: Click on the \"Sign In\" button at the top right corner of the page and enter your Roku account credentials.\n\n3. **Access your account**: Once signed in, click on your username at the top right corner, then select \"My Account\" from the dropdown menu.\n\n4. **Navigate to the \"My Linked Devices\" section**: In your account page, scroll down to the \"My Linked Devices\" section. You'll see a list of all the devices linked to your Roku account.\n\n5. **Deactivate the device**: Find the device you want to deactivate, and click on the \"Unlink\" button next to it. Confirm the action when prompted.\n\nAfter completing these steps, your Roku device will be deactivated and unlinked from your account. If you want to use the device again, you'll need to go through the setup process and link it to a Roku account.\n\nIf you have any issues or need further assistance, you can contact Roku customer support for help.",
